<br>
In Pre-Kunak we got Shock of Steel at level 64 and Lava bolt at level 49. The bolt did more damage and had better ratio but was limited while Shock of Swords was the best Mage nuke all around. Same with Kunark, we got Shock of Steel at level 57 and SFoS at level 59. It offered more dps and better ratio over Shock of Steel, but SoS was our best all around nuke because it didn't have LoS penalty and it was conjuration. In Luclin they gave us SoFB which was the first time mages had a fire based nuke that was conjuration. If they had continued to scale things correctly then Black Steel should have been our best all around nuke while, Sun Vortex should have been our fastest nuke and Fire Bolt could have been the ratio/dps nuke. Instead Sun Vortex is just going to look like a SoFB upgrade that was miss tagged, and Fire Bolt is going to the back of the spell book.  Way to go Verant. <br>
